{
  "texts": [
    "In the periodic gauge, we can freely identify ĉ † τ as (k) = ĉ † τ as (k + G) in formal manipulations.",
    "If we did not use the periodic gauge, then ĉ † τ as (k) is not necessarily equal to ĉ † τ as (k + G) because they could differ by a phase.",
    "This would lead to an additional layer of book-keeping when doing many-body calculations.",
    "choose the Bloch coefficients for valley K ′ according tou K ′ a;lσ (k, G) = u * Ka;lσ (-k, -G).",
    "(14)The kinetic energies obey ϵ SP K ′ a (k) = ϵ SP Ka (-k)."
  ]
}